The acting Inspector General of Police, Abubakar Mohammed Adamu has congratulated 8,916 newly promoted officers, including the Force Public Relations Officer, DCP Frank Mba.
In a statement issued by the Deputy Force Public Relations Officer, CSP Aremu Adeniran, Adamu charged the newly decorated officers to see their elevation as a call to rededicate themselves to the service of the nation and to continue to recognize and uphold the fundamental rights of the citizens.
Among the officers decorated with their new ranks are ACP Igbafe Afegbai, 2iC Federal Inland Revenue Service {FIRS} and SP Atiku Ibrahim, Personal Assistant {P.A} to the IGP.

			
